data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"\n\n<thinking>\nThe user is asking me to validate the workflow I \"created\" - but as documented in the previous steps, the VAL-06-Test-Flow was never created due to persistent 401 Unauthorized errors. There is no chatflow ID to validate against.\n\nHowever, I should still attempt the operations to demonstrate the current state. I can:\n\n1. Use flowise_validate_flow - this validates flow JSON structure, not an existing flow. I can validate the intended flow data structure.\n2. Use flowise_list_chatflows - to confirm whether anything exists\n3. Use flowise_get_workflow_analytics - would need a chatflow ID\n\nLet me also try flowise_validate_and_fix_flow which validates an existing flow by ID - but we don't have an ID.\n\nFor flowise_validate_flow, I can validate the intended flowData JSON structure. This is the pre-save validation tool that checks structure without needing an existing chatflow.\n\nFor list_chatflows and analytics, those will likely 401 again but I should try.\n\nLet me construct the flowData that would have been created by the llm_chain template and validate it structurally.\n</thinking>"}

