data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"---\n\n## VAL-06 Validation Report\n\n### Critical Context\n\n**The `VAL-06-Test-Flow` chatflow was never persisted to Flowise** — it failed creation in the previous step due to the 401 OBO token defect. There is no chatflow ID to query. However, I was able to validate the **intended flow structure** using the pre-save structural validator (`flowise_validate_flow`), which operates locally and does not require an authenticated Flowise connection.\n\n---\n\n### Step-by-Step Results\n\n| Step | Operation | Tool | Status | Detail |\n|:----:|-----------|------|:------:|--------|\n| 1 | **Validate flow structure** | `flowise_validate_flow` | ✅ | `valid: true` — 0 errors, 0 warnings |\n| 2 | **List chatflows** | `flowise_list_chatflows` | ❌ | `401 Unauthorized` — cannot confirm flow exists |\n| 3 | **Workflow analytics** | `flowise_get_workflow_analytics` | ❌ | `401 Unauthorized` — cannot retrieve analytics |\n\n---\n\n### Validation Report Detail\n\nThe structural validator confirmed the `llm_chain` flow definition is **well-formed and valid**:\n\n| Check | Result | Detail |\n|-------|:------:|--------|\n| **Overall validity** | ✅ Pass | `valid: true` |\n| **Errors** | 0 | No structural errors detected |\n| **Warnings** | 0 | No warnings |\n| **Total nodes** | 3 | `chatOpenAgentic_0`, `promptTemplate_0`, `llmChain_0` |\n| **Total edges** | 2 | Model→Chain, Prompt→Chain |\n| **Node positions** | ✅ | All nodes have valid `{x, y}` coordinates |\n| **Node dimensions** | ✅ | All nodes have `width: 300`, `height: 150` |\n| **Edge references** | ✅ | All edges reference existing node IDs |\n| **Edge types** | ✅ | All edges use `buttonedge` type |\n| **baseClasses** | ✅ | Properly declared on all nodes |\n\n**Validated flow architecture:**\n\n```diagram\n{\n  \"type\": \"flowchart\",\n  \"title\": \"VAL-06-Test-Flow — Validated Structure\",\n  \"layout\": \"horizontal\",\n  \"nodes\": [\n    {\"id\": \"model\", \"label\": \"chatOpenAgentic_0\\ngemini-2.0-flash-001\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"primary\"},\n    {\"id\": \"prompt\", \"label\": \"promptTemplate_0\\n\\\"You are a helpful assistant...\\\"\", \"shape\": \"document\", \"color\": \"info\"},\n    {\"id\": \"chain\", \"label\": \"llmChain_0\\n(output node)\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"success\"}\n  ],\n  \"edges\": [\n    {\"source\": \"model\", \"target\": \"chain\", \"label\": \"model handle\", \"style\": \"solid\"},\n    {\"source\": \"prompt\", \"target\": \"chain\", \"label\": \"prompt handle\", \"style\": \"solid\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Assessment\n\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> **The flow definition is structurally valid**, but it **does not exist in Flowise**. Validation only confirms the JSON schema, node connectivity, and field completeness — it cannot confirm runtime behavior because the flow was never deployed.\n\n**What passed:**\n- ✅ **Structural validation** — The `llm_chain` flow data is correctly formed with 3 nodes, 2 edges, proper positions, dimensions, baseClasses, and handle references. It would work if successfully persisted.\n\n**What could not be tested:**\n- ❌ **Existence confirmation** — `flowise_list_chatflows` returned 401; cannot verify the flow appears in the catalog\n- ❌ **Runtime analytics** — `flowise_get_workflow_analytics` returned 401; no execution data exists regardless (flow was never deployed)\n- ❌ **End-to-end prediction** — Cannot run `flowise_run_prediction` against a non-existent chatflow\n\n---\n\n### Blocker Summary\n\nAll three validation steps that require an authenticated Flowise connection remain blocked by the same **P0 defect** identified in the previous step:\n\n```\nOBO Token Present in MCP Context  ──✅──▶  MCP Proxy  ──❌──▶  Flowise API (token not forwarded)\n                                                                    │\n                                                                    └── 401 Unauthorized\n```\n\n| Defect | Impact | Status |\n|--------|--------|:------:|\n| **OBO token not forwarded** | All authenticated Flowise operations fail | ❌ Open — P0 |\n| **Flowise gateway unhealthy** | `get_framework_status` confirms endpoint down | ❌ Open — P0 |\n| **Health check false positive** | `flowise_health_check` says healthy while API is down | ⚠️ Open — P1 |\n\nUntil the P0 token-forwarding defect is resolved, no Flowise workflow can be created, listed, validated against the live store, or analyzed. The structural pre-save validator is the only Flowise tool currently functional for authenticated users."}

